cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.LT, cs.SE, cs.TL 

The paper discusses the synthesis of domain theory, concurrency theory, and logics of programs, which are all topics related to mathematical foundations of computer science. The use of Stone duality and the focus on observable properties suggest a connection to logic and topology, hence cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) are likely categories. The paper also discusses the interpretation of types as propositional theories, which suggests a connection to cs.LT (Automata and Formal Languages). The focus on denotational semantics and the use of metalanguage suggest a connection to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.TL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory).
